We still remember the intriguing reasons given to us by our friend, the late Gilbert Miller, who always insisted on the magnum size or larger. We quote Mr. Miller, ‘Not only are big bottles more impressive and festive, but the wines develop more slowly and therefore will live longer in the larger bottle. And the wine steward thus makes fewer trips to the table since he gets more glasses out of each bottle — and not unimportantly, the temptation to pilfer is reduced because who can conceal
